    <header class="mb-8">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">What is an API?</h1>
      <p class="text-lg">An <b>API</b> (Application Programming Interface) is like a digital waiter: it takes your request, brings it to another service (the kitchen), and delivers the result—without you needing to know how everything works behind the scenes.</p>
    </header>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-2">How Does an API Work?</h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside mb-4">
        <li>You make a request (like checking the weather).</li>
        <li>The API delivers your request to another service.</li>
        <li>The service responds through the API.</li>
        <li>You get the answer.</li>
      </ol>
      <button onclick="showAPIDemo()" class="bg-blue-500 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded shadow hover:bg-blue-600">See a Demo</button>
      <div id="api-demo" class="hidden mt-4">
